  "text": "In terms of propagation modeling on a city-wide scale, studies reported by Giordano et al. [CITATION_1] and Cozzetti et al. [CITATION_2] focus on computationally efficient propagation modeling in grid-like urban environments, where streets are assumed to be straight and intersecting at a right angle. While such assumptions hold for certain urban areas, in others they might not (e.g., in the city of Porto - Fig. 4) .",
